        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(auth): cooldown inline api key billing failures",
        "body": "## Summary\n- record provider-level cooldown state for inline `models.providers.<id>.apiKey` credentials\n- block literal, env-marker, and env SecretRef inline API keys while provider-level auth/billing cooldown is active\n- keep healthy stored auth profiles available as fallback when an inline provider key is cooling down\n- preserve inline provider cooldown usage state across auth-store load/merge pruning\n\nCloses #39807.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- **Behavior addressed**: Inline provider API keys without auth profiles now record billing/auth failures under a provider-level usage id, skip immediate reuse during cooldown, and become available again after cooldown expiry. Env-backed inline keys use the same cooldown gate, while healthy stored profiles for the provider remain available.\n- **Real environment tested**: Local Linux checkout rebased on upstream/main at 5b310a7b27 with branch head 6db13645ab.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n  - `node --import tsx -e '<local inline-api-key cooldown probe using AuthProfileStore, markInlineProviderApiKeyFailure, and getProviderAuthOption>'`\n  - `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/auth-profiles.markauthprofilefailure.test.ts src/agents/model-auth.profiles.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/assistant-failover.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner.run-embedded-agent.auth-profile-rotation.e2e.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n  - `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/agents/auth-profiles/persisted.ts src/agents/auth-profiles/store.ts src/agents/auth-profiles/usage.ts src/agents/auth-profiles.ts src/agents/model-auth.ts src/agents/model-auth.profiles.test.ts src/agents/auth-profiles.markauthprofilefailure.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/assistant-failover.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/assistant-failover.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner.run-embedded-agent.auth-profile-rotation.e2e.test.ts`\n  - `git diff --check`\n- **Evidence after fix**: Terminal output from the local inline API key cooldown probe:\n  ```text\n  { keys: [ 'inline-api-key:demo-local' ], until: 1780245179166 }\n  threw Inline API key for provider \"demo-local\" is temporarily disabled after a provider auth/billing failure. Retry after about 1 minute, or switch to a different auth profile/API key.\n  ```\n  Supplemental checks also passed: agents Vitest shard 3 files / 106 tests, e2e Vitest shard 1 file / 28 tests, oxfmt on touched files, and `git diff --check`.\n- **Observed result after fix**: The production auth-store persisted the inline provider cooldown under `inline-api-key:demo-local`, then model auth rejected immediate reuse of that provider's inline key with the expected temporary-disabled auth/billing message. Regression coverage also verifies env-backed inline keys reject during cooldown, assistant/runner no-profile billing paths mark provider-level cooldown, and stored provider profiles still resolve when the inline key is cooling down.\n- **What was not tested**: A live paid-provider 402 against a real exhausted account; the local probe exercises production auth-store and model-auth paths without intentionally triggering real billing failures.\n\n## Background\nThis replaces the closed polluted PR #80482 with the same intended auth-runtime fix rebuilt as a clean branch from current upstream/main.\n\n",
